The paper proposes a deep learning based method for salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The method utilizes both saliency and boundary features, which are common features used in computer vision tasks. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing and time series analysis, indicating a possible connection to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on public datasets, which suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) subfields.
